            %h3 Information
            %p This is an example of the collapsing Noticeboard created for the Foundry system. 
            %p Based on the Bootstrap collapsable panels, it has been styled to show a clear heirachy of information as well as badges highlighting any outstanding actions that need to completed. The To Do list is set to be open on default. 
            
            .hidden
              %p First of all the main panel should have a class of <em>.noticeboard</em> added to it.
              It has a top <em>.panel-heading</em> with just the H3 heading of Noticeboard, this has <em>.badge</em> attached that calculates the total of the badges in the following 3 sections (To Do, Waiting and Reference).
              %h3 Sections
              %p Each sections has no <em>.panel</em>, just a <em>.panel-heading</em> followed by a <em>.panel-body</em>, with a <em>.panel-footer</em> sitting WITHIN the <em>.panel-body</em>, so that footer is hidden when the panel collapses.
              Each Panel Heading has a data-toggle <em>.collapse</em>, and a data-target and href of it's ID (#todo, #waiting or #reference). Each Section Panel Body also needs the relative ID added to it as well as the class of <em>.collapse</em>. The first section (To Do) should also have the class of <em>.in</em> added to it's Panel Body, so that it is open at refresh.
              %br
              Each panel header also had a badge with a class of it's ID name. (<em>.todo</em>, <em>.waiting</em> or <em>.reference</em>)
              %br
              %br
              %p Each Section has the articles within the Panel Body in this order.
              <em>.notice-article</em> and within that, 
              %br 
              &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>.notice-date</em> (only at the top), 
              %br 
              &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>.notice-text</em> 
              %br 
              &nbsp;&nbsp;<em>.notice-link</em>
              %br
              %br
              %p Each article is serapted by a DIV with a class of <em>.divide-dots</em>.
              %br
              %p And finishes of with a Panel Footer with the Panel Body. 

    



